been developed on one girl. No patient required reintervention during follow up 
and there was no late mortality. Almost all of our patients were asymptomatic, 
had normal activity, regularly exercised and some of them participated in school 
sport programs. Complete correction of Tetralogy of Fallot showed good results 
with normal life expectancy for the patients.

